The Trump campaign announced on Tuesday that President Trump will hold a rally in Green Bay, Wisconsin on April 27th.
This is the same night at the White House Correspondents’ DinnerThe Trump Campaign has announced the next Trump Rally to take place Saturday, April 27th in Green Bay, Wisconsin.
— POTUS_Schedule (@45_Schedule) April 16, 2019President Trump vowed earlier this month to skip the dinner and hold a rally.
The White House Correspondents’ Dinner honors members of the White House Correspondents’ Association, an organization of journalists who cover the White House and the President of the United States.
Trump Campaign Manager Brad Parscale weighed in on the rally.